{
  "texts": [
    "The inset focuses on the case N = 6.",
    "It conveys the optimization speed for four different levels of corruption, namely, 0, 2, 4, and 6 out of 6 labels being corrupted, and provides insights into the average convergence time.",
    "The shaded area denotes the variance over five experiment repetitions with independently initialized QCNN parameters.",
    "Surprisingly, on average, fitting completely random noise takes less time than fitting unperturbed data.",
    "This phenomenon emphasizes that QCNNs can accurately memorize random data."
  ]
}